appendPVFields

public void appendPVFields(PVField[] pvFields)
Description copied from interface: PVStructure
Append a PVField[]. Each element of the array must have been created with this PVStructure as the parent. For a javaIOC record. This should only be called when a record is in the readyForInitialization state.

Specified by:
appendPVFields in interface PVStructure
Parameters:
pvFields - The fields to append. Note that if the original number of fields is 0 than pvFields replaces the original. Thus the caller must NOT reuse pvFields after calling this method.
